markdown: <::attestation: Postmark, postage stamp, and cancellation mark Status: Mailed/Processed Readable Text: NEW YORK, JAN 12, 430PM, 1954; UNITED STATES POSTAGE, GEORGE WASHINGTON, 1 CENT; POSTAL CARD, 1, WASHINGTON; THIS SIDE OF CARD IS FOR ADDRESS Description: A postmark from New York dated January 12, 1954, 4:30 PM, is positioned to the left of a 1-cent United States postage stamp featuring George Washington. A cancellation mark, reading "POSTAL CARD" and "1" with "WASHINGTON", overlaps the stamp and extends to the right. Below these, a rectangular box contains the text "THIS SIDE OF CARD IS FOR ADDRESS".::> Dr. Robert E. Shank Department of Preventive Medicine & Public Health Washington University School of Medicine Euclid Ave. & Kingshighway St. Louis 10, Missouri Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/rjgg0227
